    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Hebrews",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 13,
        "summary": "Marriage is honorable\u2014Christ is the same everlastingly\u2014Paul explains how the Saints are to offer acceptable sacrifices.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Let brotherly love continue.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence; Love.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hospitality.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stranger.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Angels; Translated Beings.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 24:16 (13\u201316, 28).",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them; and them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 25:36; Col. 4:18.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Marriage is honourable in all, and the bed undefiled: but whoremongers and adulterers God will judge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Marry; Marriage, Temporal.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Whore.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adulterer.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let your conversation be without covetousness; and be content with such things as ye have: for he hath said, I will never leave thee, nor forsake thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contentment.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 1:5; 1\u00a0Kgs. 6:13.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So that we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember them which have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of their conversation.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and to day, and for ever.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Eternal Nature of.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not carried about with divers and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with meats, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 11:3; Col. 2:8.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 4:14.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "We have an altar, whereof they have no right to eat which serve the tabernacle.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the bodies of those beasts, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sin, are burned without the camp.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people with his own blood, suffered without the gate.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sanctification.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blood, Symbolism of.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 19:17 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0outside of. Lev. 4:12.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let us go forth therefore unto him without the camp, bearing his reproach.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reproach.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For here have we no continuing city, but we seek one to come.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of our lips giving thanks to his name.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:108.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 57:19.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 9:12 (7\u201312).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that is unprofitable for you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sustaining Church Leaders.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Submissiveness.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 184,
                        "end": 186
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conscience.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Good Shepherd; Shepherd.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0New and Everlasting Covenant.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 141
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covenants.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Make you perfect in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is wellpleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Will of.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I beseech you, brethren, suffer the word of exhortation: for I have written a letter unto you in few words.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Know ye that our brother Timothy is set at liberty; with whom, if he come shortly, I will see you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy salute you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Grace be with you all. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}